# Secret-name patterns for the ai-tools sandbox.
#
# Both root helpers read this file and treat a path whose BASENAME matches any
# pattern below as a credential file:
#   - ai-tools-chown  (PostToolUse/Stop handback) quarantines agent-written
#     matches to <you>:<you> 600, revoking ai-tools' read access.
#   - ai-tools-lockdown (manual `sudo ai-tools-lockdown` sweep) sets matches to
#     file 600 / dir 700, owner <you>:ai-tools, across the current project.
#
# This file is owned <you>:<you> 600. You may edit it; ai-tools cannot read or
# write it (it is neither owner nor group, and cannot enter the 700
# .config/ai-tools directory) -- the root helpers read it on your behalf.
#
# Format:
#   - one pattern per line; '#' starts a comment; blank lines ignored
#   - patterns are BASENAME globs (no '/'), matched case-insensitively
#   - '*' matches any characters; '.' is literal
#
# Keep patterns anchored to a name or an environment segment. Avoid broad
# catch-alls like '*.*.json' / '*.*.config': those also match .NET build
# artifacts the toolchain must read (MyApp.deps.json, MyApp.runtimeconfig.json,
# project.assets.json, MyApp.dll.config), and quarantining them breaks builds.
#
# If this file is removed, the helpers fall back to a built-in default list
# identical to the entries below.

# --- dotenv / environment ---
.env
.env.*
env
.environment
.environment.*
environment

# --- generic secret / credential names ---
secret
secrets
usersecrets
private
secret.*
secrets.*
*.secret
*.credential
credential
credentials
credentials.*

# --- SSH / private keys ---
id_rsa
id_dsa
id_ecdsa
id_ed25519
authorized_keys

# --- key / certificate / keystore material ---
*.ppk
*.pem
*.key
*.priv
*.p12
*.pfx
*.crt
*.pkcs12
*.jks
*.keystore
*.p8
*.asc
*.gpg

# --- tool credential files ---
kubeconfig
.pgpass
.git-credentials
.dockercfg
.htpasswd
.npmrc
.pypirc
.netrc

# --- .NET configuration carrying secrets (name-anchored) ---
connectionstrings.*.json
ConnectionString.*.config
commonsettings.*.json
CommonSettings.*.config
appsettings.*.json
AppSettings.*.config
web.*.config
App.*.config

# --- environment-qualified config (any extension) ---
*.DEV.*
*.STAGE.*
*.PROD.*
*.C1_DEV.*
*.C2_STAGE.*
*.C3_PROD.*
*.Development.*
*.Staging.*
*.Production.*
